
[1]hemorrhoids

   HEM'ORRHOIDS, n. [Gr. blood, and a flowing.] A discharge of blood from
   the vessels of the anus; the piles; in Scripture, emerods.

   The term is also applied to tumors formed by a morbid dilatation of the
   hemorrhoidal veins. When they do not discharge blood,they are called
   blind piles; when they occasionally emit blood, bleeding or open piles.
